==English==

===Etymology===
First attested [[w:1812|1812]]. Common [[folklore]] holds that his origins come from the men of an army base in [[Troy]], [[New York]], who would receive [[barrel]]s of meat stamped with the initials U.S. The soldiers [[joke|jokingly]] referred to it as the initials of the meat [[supply|supplier]], '''Uncle Samuel Wilson'''.

===Proper noun===
{{en-proper noun}}
{{wikipedia}}
# {{US}} A [[personification]] of the [[United States]] [[government]].
#: '''''Uncle Sam''' Needs You!'' means  ''The [U.S.] Army Needs You!''

